begin
theorem
Th4: (for X,Y being RealNormSpace holds (for f being  bounded (LinearOperator of X,Y) holds ((f is_Lipschitzian_on (the carrier of X) & f is_continuous_on (the carrier of X)) & (for x being (Point of X) holds f is_continuous_in x))))
proof
let X being RealNormSpace,Y being RealNormSpace;
let f being  bounded (LinearOperator of X,Y);
consider K being Real such that A1: ( 0 ) <= K and A2: (for x being (VECTOR of X) holds ||. ( f . x ) .|| <= ( K * ||. x .|| )) by LOPBAN_1:def 8;
A3:now
let x being (Point of X),y being (Point of X);
assume that
x in (the carrier of X)
and
y in (the carrier of X);
( ( f /. x ) - ( f /. y ) ) = ( ( f . x ) + ( ( - 1 ) * ( f . y ) ) ) by RLVECT_1:16;
then ( ( f /. x ) - ( f /. y ) ) = ( ( f . x ) + ( f . ( ( - 1 ) * y ) ) ) by LOPBAN_1:def 5;
then ( ( f /. x ) - ( f /. y ) ) = ( f . ( x + ( ( - 1 ) * y ) ) ) by GRCAT_1:def 8;
then A4: ( ( f /. x ) - ( f /. y ) ) = ( f . ( x + ( - y ) ) ) by RLVECT_1:16;
||. ( ( f /. x ) - ( f /. y ) ) .|| <= ( ( K * ||. ( x - y ) .|| ) + ||. ( x - y ) .|| ) by A2,A4,XREAL_1:38;
hence ||. ( ( f /. x ) - ( f /. y ) ) .|| <= ( ( K + 1 ) * ||. ( x - y ) .|| );
end;
( dom f ) = (the carrier of X) by FUNCT_2:def 1;
hence f is_Lipschitzian_on (the carrier of X) by A1,A3,NFCONT_1:def 9;
hence A5: f is_continuous_on (the carrier of X) by NFCONT_1:45;
hereby
let x being (Point of X);
( f | (the carrier of X) ) = f by RELSET_1:19;
hence f is_continuous_in x by A5,NFCONT_1:def 7;
end;
end;
